 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzebanar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#333333>(10/18/02 11:55:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Absor, we need info on our PoP pets. </span><hr size=1> I noticed at castersrealm, a Verant employee was interviewed regarding the new weapons, and he had the following to say about casters + spells:<br>
<br>
&quot;As for casters specifically, we have a few interesting trick up our sleeves that you’ll probably like. And we have indeed been receiving your comments about the proposed spells, thank you for sending them in. We’ll be tightening up the spells for the expansion over the next few weeks.<br>
<br>
Thanks for playing our game. &quot;<br>
<br>
It would be wonderful if some kind of information could be given out about our pets, so that we might give feedback about them as we've been doing with other spells. They are the most important aspect of our class, and probably the most potent aspect.<br>
<br>
If they aren't properly balanced now, before PoP is released, it will be incredibly difficult to do so afterwards, after we've been tweaked with Powerful rains, powerful DDs, and new high level summons. <br>
<br>
Lets get it all out of the way before its released, and make all of our lives a bit happier afterwards.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulittlestgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Littlest Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 12:28:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Absor, we need info on our PoP pets. </span><hr size=1> Very good observation, particularly if you relate our pet to being escentially a very big and powerful DoT. I like to call him Gontik, but still... you get the idea. <br>
<br>
How does our pet scale from previous pets? How do they compare to our Epic? How do they compare to OTHER people's pets? It's information I'm sure we'd all love to know regardless of our school of thought. <br>
<br>
I don't foresee this information being released prior to PoP going live however. And to that effect, I'm quite sure my pet will still be every bit the personal leg-breaker he's always been for me. I can, if I have to, wait on sorting out all the details until later.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uintriguethemagician.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Intrigue the Magician</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 1:33:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not so sure it is really details we need</span><hr size=1> What we really need is just some confermation that our epic pet is still going to be epic, ie the best of the best, I hope. Other pets for specific functions is super but the epic should be just that. EPIC in all respects. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzebanar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zebanar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 6:20:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I replied about this in another thread...</span><hr size=1> I mentioned this aspect of things in another thread...<br>
<br>
I think overall the epic should be, on average a better pet. <br>
<br>
Better for soloing due to the DS and the procs<br>
<br>
however, for situations, such as fighting caster mobs, or wanting to do simply massive damage, the new pets would be better options. I think this would be best for all parties. It pleases both the people who have no epic pet, and those with the epic have new ulitiy and function and get the most out of their new pet.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uomegasyphon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 511<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 6:28:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> comment</span><hr size=1> i hope epic is not best of the 4 new pets. a 2 year old pet does not sit well with each new expansion. you gotta stop equating epic to the best pet we should get because its just not the case. why would anyone want a level 49 pet trying its hardest to maybe hit a mob 10 levels higher then it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglicdaboomaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glicdaboomaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(10/20/02 5:10:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: comment</span><hr size=1> To be quite honest with you I'm sick of the epic pet, I'd be more then happy to frequently see my fire pet again..... gosh I don't even remember what the fire pet looks like it's been so long...<br>
